size_t

data type

- unsigned integer type defined in [stddefh.]
    - not a keyword of language itself
- represents vals in range [0, SIZE_MAX]
    - SIZE_MAX defined in [stdint.h]
- for sizes, cardinalities, etc.
    - e.g. sizeof returns int of type size_t
- printf-specifier: %zu

- SEE ALSO
    - modern, lvl.1.4/1.5

EXAMPLE
printf("%zu", SIZE_MAX); // 18446744073709551615 == 2^64 - 1

char a[3];
printf("%zu\n", sizeof a); // 3
